Commentary: Afridi starts with a good length ball just outside off, the ball moves away a hint as Burns shoulders arms.
Slightly short but outside off again, another leave by Burns.
FOUR! First runs for England and Burns. He will be relieved! A good length ball outside off, Burns with soft hands runs it down through point and gully to bag a boundary.
A muted appeal but nothing from the umpire. Good length ball on the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal made for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
Good length ball just outside off, Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Dot to end! Good start for both the sides. Good length ball just outside off, Burns first tries to play at it but hangs his bat in the end to allow it go to the keeper.
Play and a miss! Abbas is on the money right away! He starts his spell with a good length ball just outside off, Sibley plays at it away from his body to get beaten.
Sibley is up and running as well. Timed superbly! Full and on middle and leg, he whips it through mid-wicket and takes three before the fielder can chase and cut it off.

A couple for Burns. A good length ball around off, Burns tucks it behind square on the leg side. Naseem from fine leg was a bit slow in getting to the ball and that allowed the batters to return for the second run.
Little wide outside off, easy leave for Burns.
Fullish and around off, Burns forces it towards point where Masood makes a diving stop to his left.
Good length ball around off and middle, Burns plays it back to the bowler with a solid defense.
Fullish and outside off, luring the batsman to go for the drive but Sibley is not interested as he lets it go to the keeper.
Landed fuller and around off, Sibley keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, Sibley drives it past the cover fielder who chases it and keeps it down to one.
Little wide outside off for Burns to play at that.
Way wide outside off on a fuller length. Goes past the batsman as he shoulders arms. The ball moves away a bit as Rizwan dives to his left to collect as the ball dies down.
Good length ball on middle and leg, played towards the off side.
Good length ball around off, guided towards the gully region with soft hands.
Slightly shortish and around off, Sibley plays it towards the off side off his back foot and calls for the single but Burns sees Fawad charging at the ball so sends him back.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Landed around off, blocked off the front foot.
Angled in from outside off on a shortish length, Sibley tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Full and on middle, Sibley flicks it to the man at square leg.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley looks to defend but the ball hits the upper part of the bat and goes to fine leg for a single.

OUT! That has gone straight into the hands, feels the third umpire. The soft signal was out as well so nothing much for the third umpire to check. Shaheen Afridi has drawn the first blood and takes down Burns once again. Good length ball around off, Burns pokes at it but with hard hands. This time the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes to Shan Masood at fourth slip. He gets down and pouches the catch. Burns is not sure if that carried but Masood signals it's out. The umpires get together and refer it upstairs with soft signal being out. The replays confirm the same and Burns has to go.
FOUR! Perfect way to get off the mark! A juicy full ball on middle and leg, Crawley whips it through mid-wicket and starts his innings with a boundary.
Good leave! That was really close. Good length ball just outside off, Crawley covers his stumps and lets it be. More on the length than the line.

FOUR! That was the magic ball but Crawley squirted it away through the slip cordon to get another boundary. Yorker around off, Crawley gets his bat down in time to dig it out and it goes through the cordon for another boundary. 9 runs off it but most importantly, a wicket for Pakistan.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
FOUR! Nicely played from Sibley! He is looking good so far! On a length on middle, Sibley flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Hits the thigh pad! Brilliant delivery from Abbas! Good length ball around off, moving away. Sibley looks to defend but gets squared up. He gets beaten and gets hit on the thigh pads.
BEATEN! Beautiful from Abbas! On a length outside off, Sibley looks to put bat on it but misses it altogether.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Outside off, not played at.
Another ball on the pads of Crawley, he powerfully works it through mid-wicket for 3 more. He moves to 11 in just 4 balls.
Ripper! Fuller and just around off, Sibley looks to defend but the ball swings away as it comes closer to the bat to beat the outside edge.
Shortish and around off, forced towards point by Sibley and a loud call of no for the run.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Sibley tries to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad.
Full and around off, this time Sibley is solid in defense.
Landed around middle on a good length, played back to the bowler.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards the cover fielder by Crawley.
BEATEN! That is an unplayable delivery from Abbas! Good carry to the keeper as well! Good length ball around off, moving away. Crawley looks to defend but it swings away and gets beaten.
On a good length on middle, Crawley dances down and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A single taken! Good batting! Full delivery on off, Crawley pushes it to cover and collects a single.
Good length ball outside off, Dom watches the ball carefully and leaves it alone.
Abbas dishes a full delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Crawley prods forward and blocks it to cover.
Around off, blocked.
Outside off, left alone this time.
Fuller and outside off, Crawley looks to drive it towards the off side but the ball comes in a little late and that means it goes through mid off. A couple taken.

Oh! That was not too far away from the off stump. It is on the fuller length and just around off, comes back in but Crawley is confident that he is covering his stumps and shoulders arms. Any leave is a good leave if that is not scattering the wickets.
This time he comes forward and blocks the fuller ball around off.
Good length ball on off, Sibley plays it to cover and takes a single.
EDGY! Lucky for Crawley! Good length ball around off, Crawley comes down the pitch and looks to defend. It takes the edge and goes towards fine leg. A couple taken.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley pushes it back to the bowler.
Too high! Nicely bowled! Good length ball on off, angling in. Crawley looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Full delivery on middle, Zak works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Crawley blocks it to point for another dot.
Nicely played! Floated ball on middle, Sibley dances down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Flatter one outside off, Sibley punches it through the cover region for a single.
Short delivery outside off, Crawley punches it to cover.
Floated outside off, Crawley rocks on his back foot and drives it through the cover-point region. Before the fielder can cut it off, the batters take two.
Loopy ball on middle, Crawley defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off, Crawley plays it to deep cover for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley defends it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Zak lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley offers no shot to this one.
On a length on off, Crawley looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes through gully. Two taken before the fielder cuts it off.
Good length ball on middle, Zak works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Floated on off, Crawley drives it back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Zak prods forward and pushes it to the fielder at mid off.
Looped up ball outside off, Crawley punches it to cover.
FOUR! SMASHED! Crawley has made a good start and he needs to make full use of it! Short and outside off, Crawley thrashes it through the cover region for a boundary.
Flatter on off, Crawley pushes it to long off for a single.
Tossed up ball on middle, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Naseem begins his spell with a shortish ball outside off, Sibley lets it be.

Another one little too wide outside off, left alone. Well, that wasn't as simple as it may sound. After going past the batsman, the ball comes back in and Rizwan had to dive a little to his left to collect.
This is an easy leave as it is  fuller but wide outside off. This one goes straight in the mitts.
Another one outside off on a good length, Sibley shoulders arms.
Goes full but this is on the pads, Sibley works it towards fine leg for a single.
Very full and just outside off, Crawley keeps it out.
Floated on off, Sibley pushes it to cover.
Flighted on middle, Sibley uses his feet and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Flatter one on middle, Dom defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter on off, Sibley drives it straight to mid off for a single.
Driven through mid off by the batsman. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Floated on middle, Sibley flicks it to the deep mid-wicket region for a couple.
FOUR! Poor bowling! Good length ball on the pads, Crawley flicks it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Zak defends it out onto the pitch.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.

Three now! Full delivery outside off, Crawley leans forward and drives it through the extra cover region! 50-run partnership is up. This has been good from these two. They have looked good so far and will look to continue.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, not played at.
Tossed up on off, Crawley defends it to cover.
Full and outside off, Crawley pushes it to long off for a single.
Tossed up ball on middle, Sibley comes down the track and drives it to mid on. They think of a single but decide against it.
On the pads, Sibley tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Looped up ball on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, Zak works it to the leg side for a single.

FOUR! Nicely done! Fuller and outside off, Crawley allows the ball to come to him and then gently pushes at it. It goes through gully for another boundary. Runs coming nicely for the hosts. It was off the outside edge but gentle hands meant that it went along the ground.
FOUR! Yes, the runs are coming thick and fast. Naseem bowls it short and just outside off, Crawley goes back quickly and powers it through mid-wicket to bag another boundary.
A block to follow the two boundaries on this fuller ball.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the gully fielder.
Full and around off again, Crawley watchfully defends it.
Firmly punched but straight to mid off. Another excellent over for England, 8 runs coming from it.
Full and around middle, Sibley flicks it towards mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and Sibley has to go. England lose a review as well. Sibley looked troubled a bit against Yasir and he has got his man. Yasir tosses this up around off and middle, Sibley comes down the track and looks to slam it through the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. A massive appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger after taking his sweet time. Sibley and Crawley get together and refer it upstairs. The replays roll in and the Ultra Edge detects no bat. And, it is three reds on the Ball Tracker so Sibley has to go. He takes a review along with him. Pakistan break the threatening stand.
The skipper is off the mark as the first ball he faces is short and wide outside off, he punches it to deep cover for a single.
Full and on middle, Crawley keeps it out.
Another full ball, pushed towards mid on.
Short and outside off, Crawley punches it well but finds mid off. End of a successful over for Yasir and Pakistan.
Ripper! Shortish and just outside off, Root is on the back foot to play at it but is beaten for the outside edge.
Another play and a miss! This is again around off on a good length, Root pokes again to get beaten.

Gets to the other end this time by gently forcing this good length ball on middle towards mid off. The fielder there was slow and the cry from the keeper of 'Come on, yar' was heard. Pakistan would love to bowl more balls to the new man on the crease.

Poor from Crawley! He could've easily left that alone but he has been in good nick so far so he goes after this fuller ball outside off without any foot movement. A hint of away movement as well. He looks to drive but misses.
Like Root, after getting beaten, Crawley works this ball on the leg side to get to the other end.
Dot to end as Root is solid on the front foot to block the last ball of the over.
Flatter and around off, Crawley is on the back foot to punch it towards mid off.
Tosses this full and just outside off, Crawley looks to defend but gets beaten.
Nicely bowled! He is forcing the batsman to play on the back foot. Bowls it little short and around off, Crawley does well to get his bat down in time to block.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish and around off, this one is punched away to long off for a single.
Quicker and slightly shorter, Root is on the back foot to punch it to deep cover for a single. Quality over from Yasir as he made the batsmen do what he wanted to do.
Fuller and around off, Root drives it towards deep cover for a couple of runs.
Ouch! A short ball around middle, Root looks to sit under it but it just doesn't bounce. Root does well to realize that and somehow fend it off towards the leg side.
Short and outside off, Root finds point.

Edged but fell short. A fuller length ball around off, Root plays at it with soft hands. A thick outside edge is induced but it falls way ahead of Yasir at third slip. Hits his hands and goes behind and the batters cross for a single.
Shortish one on the body, Crawley tucks it towards fine leg to move to 48.
Good length ball around off, Root keeps it out off his front foot.
Floated outside off, Crawley pushes it to cover.
Tossed up outside off, Crawley pushes it to deep cover for a single.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Floated on off, Root prods forward and looks to defend. He misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. The  replays show that there was a big inside edge on that one.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Quicker one on off, Root manages to defend it to the off side.
Outside off, Root drives it to deep cover for a single.
Full delivery on the pads, Root flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery outside off, Crawley has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley thinks of playing it at first but then leaves it alone.
Outside off, Crawley makes another leave to this one.
Make that 5th continuous leave in the over! Good length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Loopy ball on off, Root prods forward and defends it to cover.
PLAY AND A MISS! Played this shot on width! Flatter ball outside off, Root moves inside his crease and then looks to cut but fails to make any connection.
On off, pushed to cover.
Loopy ball on the pads, Root works it to square leg.
Flighted on middle, Root blocks it to the bowler.
BEATEN! Almost another wicket for Yasir! He is bowling really well! He digs one outside off, Root goes back and looks to cut but misses it altogether.
Afridi bowls another one outside off, Crawley has to wait to get to his fifty as he leaves it alone.
Full delivery outside off, Crawley pushes it to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.

Patience runs out for Crawley! Brilliant bowling from Afridi! He kept on bowling outside off to Crawley to test his patience and it almost worked! Shaheen dishes a good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to drive but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley leaves it alone.
Flatter one on off, Root pushes it to cover.
Tossed up outside off, Root leans forward and drives it to the cover fielder.
Low full toss on off, Root pushes it to extra cover where the fielder makes a good stop.
Outside off, not played at.
Flatter one on middle, Root blocks it back to the bowler.
A couple now! Tossed up on the pads, Root tucks it towards the deep square leg region for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, angling in. Crawley solidly defends it to point.
BEATEN! Lovely piece of bowling from Afridi! Good length ball around off, Crawley prods forward to defend but fails to make any connection.
Full delivery outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Another one outside off, Crawley does not bother to play at that one.

FOUR! 4th Test fifty for Crawley comes up in some style! Back-to-back 50s for him! He has played well so far and will look for a big one here! He started batting positively and has settled down comfortably. Afridi dishes a full delivery on off, Crawley creams the drive through mid off for a boundary. He was made to wait for this but he didn't get too irritated and has got the milestone exactly the way he opened his account, i.e. with a boundary. WITH THAT IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 1.

Runs to begin the second session for Root and England! Short and outside off from Abbas, Root punches it through the covers and runs three before the fielder can get around the ball and return it to the keeper.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards gully.
In the channel outside off, Crawley shoulders arms.
Fullish and closer to the off pole but Crawley is sure about his timbers as he lets it go to the keeper once again.
Dot to end! Three from the first over of the second session. Fuller and around off, Crawley comes forward and bunts it on the off side.
Short and outside off, Root goes on the back foot and cuts but finds the point fielder.

Play and a miss! Short and outside off, Root goes after it but misses. There is a muted appeal from the bowler but not out says the umpire. Only the bowler looked interested and hence no review from Pakistan.
Little wide outside off, this time Root shoulders arms.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shortish and outside off, Root is on the back foot to run it down through gully to get a boundary. Just opened the blade there at the last moment, did Root.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid on.
Beaten! Just outside off on a good length, Root looks to force it on the off side but misses to get beaten.

Play and a miss! That shaped away nicely! Abbas bangs it short and around off, Crawley pokes at it but the ball moves away to beat the outside edge. Rizwan gets the ball and fires the throw at the striker's end. He does so with the gloves on but misses. Both the batters are batting out of the crease so Rizwan kind of tries to tell them that he is watching them.
Good length ball around off, Crawley looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the pads.
This time a solid block off the front foot.
Wide outside off, Crawley lets it be by coming forward.
Angled in from way outside off, left alone.
Leave on the last ball as well as it goes away from outside off on a good length. Maiden from Abbas.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid on.

FOUR! Poor ball and punished! Plenty of width outside off, Root hammers it over backward point to get another boundary. He moves to 21 with that. The boundary takes Root's runs against Pakistan over 1000. 100 is up as well for England.
Goes short and on middle, a better one from Naseem. Root goes back and pulls it towards fine leg by rolling his wrists for a single.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Shortish and around off, Crawley gets it off the inner half towards square leg for a single.

In the channel outside off, testing the patience of Crawley, like they did in the 2nd phase of the first session. Crawley, like he controlled himself in that session, does so again and shoulders arms.
Landed around off on a fuller length, blocked.

Risky single! Shortish and around middle, Zak tucks it towards mid on and calls for a single. The fielder gets to the ball and fires the throw but misses. Misses the stumps but hits the batter near his ankle. Replays suggested Crawley was home though.
Wide outside off on a length, left alone.
Another quick single! This is good batting from Root. He gently pushes it towards mid on and calls for a single.
A leave to end the over! 2 from it.
Outside off, left alone.
Short and outside off, Root punches it firmly but can't beat the cover fielder who dives to his left to stop the ball with both hands.
Good length ball around off, this one is pushed towards the point fielder.
Little too wide outside off, Root is not going to play at these. That was 91.2 mph which is quick for a 17-year old. Can he bowl a little closer in that channel outside off to force an error?
Good length delivery around off, worked towards the leg side.
Maiden from Naseem as the last ball is left alone as it is little too wide outside off. He needs to make the batters play.
Flatter and around off, Crawley keeps it out off his back foot.
Flatter and around off, keeps low as well but Crawley manages to force it through mid off for a single.
Tossed up around off, Root keeps it out.
Shortish and around off, Root goes back and strokes it to deep cover for a single.
Another single! Yasir bowls it flatter and around off, Zak is on the back foot to slam it to long off for a single.
Single to end the over, 4 from it. Yasir bowls another short ball outside off, Root is quickly on the back foot to punch and keep the strike for the next over.
FOUR! Naseem bowls it short but the line is down the leg side. Root swivels and pulls it fine down the leg side. No chance for the fine leg fielder to cut it off.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a brilliant take from Rizwan and what a lovely ball from the teenager. Root was looking really good but falls once again after getting a good start. That was unplayable from Naseem. It lands on the perfect length and it is on the perfect line as well. Just around off and on the good length. Root looks to defend but the away movement means the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes to the right of the keeper. It is in front of the first slip fielder but Rizwan moves to his right and pouches it nicely. Good looking stand is broken again by Pakistan before it grow big.
Good length ball on off, Pope lets it go to the keeper.
On a length on off, Pope blocks it to point and takes off for a single. He is off the mark.
FOUR! That's a gorgeous drive from Zak Crawley! Brilliant batting from the right-hander! Good length ball outside off, Crawley leans forward and creams the drive through extra cover for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Flatter one on off, Pope blocks it to point.
Tossed up on off, Pope comes down the track and pushes it to mid off.
Flatter one on middle, Pope blocks it back to the bowler.
Ohh! That is a lovely piece of bowling from Yasir Shah! Floated outside off, Pope uses his feet and then looks to drive. It takes the outside edge and goes towards the slip cordon.
Flighted on middle, Pope defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, defended out onto the pitch.
Driven nicely from Crawley! Good length ball on middle, Crawley drives it through mid off and picks up three before the fielder cuts it off.
On a length on middle, bouncing a little extra. Pope fends it away to the mid-wicket region.
Full delivery on off, Pope blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Pope punches it to point.
Good length ball on off, Pope blocks it out onto the pitch.
A single to end the over! Good length ball on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pope comes forward and flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Floated delivery on off, Crawley plays it to point.
Just short! Short ball on middle, Crawley camps on his back foot and works it towards mid-wicket. It lands in front of the fielder and goes past him. Two taken.
Tossed up on middle, Crawley defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Zak pushes it to cover for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Yasir has got Pope again on the back foot! Brilliant piece of bowling from Yasir and he gets his second wicket. Yasir Shah has been terrific in this series so far and he is doing the job again for his side. Pope had to play Yasir on the front foot and he does not and that brings about his downfall. Quicker delivery on off, Pope is on the back foot to defend but misses and the ball goes onto hit the off stump. The leg spinner had dismissed Pope in the same manner in the second Test match and has got him again. Lovely.
On a good length and outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery outside off, Crawley offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on off, Zak keeps it out.
Outside off, Crawley does not bother to play at that.
On a length on middle, Crawley flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery on off, Crawley blocks it off the back foot.
Short delivery on off, Crawley cuts it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Zak defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Crawley drives it through mid off for a run.
FOUR! Buttler is off the mark in style! Yasir bowls a googly on the pads, Buttler picks it and flicks it to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Buttler prods forward and defends it to cover.
On a good length on off, Crawley blocks it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Zak offers a solid defense on this one.
On a good length on middle, Crawley keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Zak defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Crawley moves into the 70s! Brilliant shot from Crawley! This was pure timing! Good length ball on middle, Crawley flicks it to the deep square leg region for another boundary.
Careful, Zak! Good length ball on off, Crawley looks to defend but it takes the bottom edge and almost goes onto the stumps. Good bowling.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Buttler defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Buttler keeps it out.
Floated delivery on middle, Buttler plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Loopy delivery on off, Buttler pushes it to mid off.
On off, Jos plays it towards mid off.
Flighted delivery on off, Buttler punches it to point.
Good length delivery on off, Crawley keeps it out.

JUST SHORT! How many times have we seen the outside edges not carrying to the slip cordon? Many times, I believe and that is the case here as well! Good length ball on off, Crawley looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip. It bounces short of the fielder. A single taken as the ball rolls towards fine leg after hittng the fielder on the hands.
FOUR! That was just a push! Buttler is in good form and will hope that he continues it in this game! Full delivery outside off, Buttler pushes it through mid off for a boundary.
BEATEN! Lovely comeback from Abbas! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

Almost! It again bounces short! Good length ball on middle, Buttler flicks it but does so uppishly. Abid tumbles ahead to take the catch but it bounces short. Pakistan think that he has caught it but Abid says that it has bounced.
Outside off, not played at.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Crawley defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Crawley looks to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Flighted delivery on off, Zak plays it to point.
Loopy delivery on off, Crawley pushes it towards point for a run.
Outside off, Buttler offers no shot to this one.
On middle, Buttler flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Good length ball on off, Crawley blocks it to cover.
Full delivery on the off stump line, Zak solidly defends it to mid off.

Got it through! Back of a length ball outside off, Crawley stands tall and punches it towards cover. Yasir dives but fails to stop. Three taken before the fielder collects it. This is Crawley's highest score in Tests, crossing 76 that he scored against West Indies in the first Test of the summer.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler watches the ball carefully and leaves the ball alone.
On a length on off, solidly blocked out onto the pitch.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Buttler.
Tossed up delivery on off, Crawley drives it to covers.
Flighted delivery on off, Crawley keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Zak blocks it off the back foot.

NOT OUT! It has bounced on the ground! Yasir bowls a flighted ball on off, Crawley looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it seems to have gone off the ground and towards the leg side. Rizwan moves to that side and collects. He is not sure whether the ball hit the ground or the boots of Zak. The umpires converge and refer it upstairs. The replays show that the ball hit the ground.
Floated on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On a good length on off, Buttler defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery outside off, Jos offers no shot to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Buttler keeps it out.
On a good length on middle, Buttler blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Jos offers a solid defense on this one.

FOUR! Whipped nicely! Floated ball on middle, Crawley whips it towards mid-wicket. There were shouts of catch it but it was wide of the fielder! Afridi chases after it and dives but fails as the ball touches the ropes.
Loopy ball outside off, Crawley pushes it to cover.
Flatter ball outside off, Crawley punches it to cover.
Tossed up on middle, Zak sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Buttler blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! There's the drive that Buttler loves to plays. He played it well in the first Test as well! Floated outside off, Buttler lunges forward and drives it through extra cover for a boundary.
Shouts of catch it but it is safe! Short ball around off, Crawley looks to pull but it takes the top edge. Luckily, it lands in between the mid-wicket and the mid on fielder. Two taken.
On off, defended off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on middle, Zak pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Short ball around off, Crawley sways away from it.
On a length on off, driven to mid off.
Tossed up delivery on off, Buttler defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Buttler punches it to point.
FOUR! This is not an easy shot to play but Buttler makes it look so easy! Flatter one outside off, Buttler creams the drive off the back foot through the cover region for a boundary.
Quicker on off, Buttler pushes it to point.
Tossed up outside off, Buttler drives it back to the bowler.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Crawley flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Afridi bowls a bouncer outside off, Buttler sways away from it.
Length delivery on leg, Buttler looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen cross ends. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
Short delivery on middle, Crawley pulls it through square leg for a run.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review as there was clearly no bat on it. Wonder what noise that Rizwan and his teammates heard. Good length ball around off, Buttler is in two minds whether to leave or defend. He does the former. Rizwan thinks that there was an edge as it passed the bat and appeals. The umpire is not interested. Azhar takes the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is nothing on it. Azhar and the umpire are involved in a laugh after the decision.
Short ball around off, Buttler sways away from it.
Tossed up delivery on off, Crawley keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Crawley blocks it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Zak defends it out.
Floated delivery on leg, Crawley looks to sweep but gets it off the pads. It goes towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs. The umpire gives it as leg byes.
On middle, Crawley flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Crawley flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length on off, Buttler defends it out.

50-run partnership comes up between the two! An important one for England. They could have easily lost more wickets but this has steadied the ship a bit. Good length ball outside off, Buttler creams the drive through extra cover for three. Can they continue on and build a big one?
Short ball on middle, Crawley blocks it out onto the ground.
FOUR! Pulled away in disdain! Shortish on middle, Crawley whacks it through square leg for a boundary. Moves to 95.
Bouncer bowled around middle, Crawley ducks under it.
Tossed up on off, Buttler pushes it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on off, Buttler looks to push but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen cross ends.
Loopy delivery on off, Crawley punches it through mid off. The batsmen take a run.
On middle, Buttler defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Buttler offers a solid block on this one.
On middle, Jos keeps it out.
Quicker one on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter on off, Zak works it to the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Crawley pushes it to point.
Flatter one on off, Crawley drives it to long off for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Buttler lunges forward and defends it out.
Flatter delivery on middle, Buttler defends it out. With that, it is TEA ON DAY 1.
Abbas starts with a good length ball on middle, Crawley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Zak pushes it back to the bowler.
Moves to 99! Good length ball on middle, Crawley flicks it to deep square leg. He runs fast and comes back for a couple. It was a bit tight but he made it in comfortably.
Full delivery outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Abbas bowls a good length ball outside the off stump line, Crawley shoulders arms to it.

First Test century for Zak Crawley! What a proud moment for him! He will never forget this moment. What an innings this has been. Hopefully, this is the first of many. Good length ball outside off, Crawley drives it through the cover region and picks up a couple to reach the milestone. Crawley has looked excellent, has not given many chances to Pakistan and has deservedly got a century.
On a good length and outside off, Buttler offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on off, Buttler dabs it towards the off side.
Outside off, Jos shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Buttler drives it to covers.
On a good length and outside off, Jos leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, Buttler does not bother to play at that.
On a good length on off, Crawley keeps it out.
Three now! Good length ball on middle, Crawley pushes it past the bowler through mid on. Afridi chases after it and slides to clean it up but cannot stop the batters from taking three.
Good length delivery outside off, Buttler offers no shot to this one.
Back of a length on middle, Buttler defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Jos offers a solid defense on this one.
Length delivery outside off, Jos lets it go.
FOUR! This is poor bowling! Sheer timing as well from Crawley! Good length ball on the pads, Crawley flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Zak blocks it of the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley blocks it to mid on.
Naseem dishes a good length delivery outside off, Crawley punches it to cover.
Crawley defends this good length ball on middle to the leg side.
NICELY PUNCHED! Good length ball outside off, Crawley rocks on his back foot and then punches it through the cover region for three.
On a good length and outside off, Crawley offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on off, Crawley punches it to covers.
Good length delivery outside off, Zak shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley defends it out.
Full again on off, Zak drives it to covers.
Outside off, Crawley leaves it alone.
Short ball around middle, Buttler ducks under it.
Short ball around middle and leg, Buttler pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Very full delivery on off, Crawley pushes it to cover.
Short ball outside off, Crawley looks to pull but fails to make any connection. That was a pacy delivery as well.
Good length ball on off, Zak defends it to point.
Short ball on middle, Zak pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up down the leg side, Crawley looks to sweep but misses it altogether.
Loopy ball on off, Crawley defends it to the cover region.
Flatter on off, Zak punches it to long off for a single.
On middle, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
That is a very good leave! Floated ball outside off, Buttler watches it carefully and leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley drives it back to the bowler who gets his boot on it to stop it. Saved some runs there.
FOUR! This one is hammered! Three fielders in the deep but Crawley still takes it on! Short ball on middle, Crawley pulls it in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on off, Crawley blocks it off the back foot onto the pitch.
On a length on middle, Crawley tucks it to square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Beautiful piece of bowling from Naseem! He needs to be regularly on this line and length! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to defend but misses it.
Back of a length ball on off, Buttler works it to mid-wicket.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Loopy ball on the pads, Crawley looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
On the pads, Crawley works it to the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Zak pushes it to point.
Flatter on off, Zak punches it to mid off for another dot.
Loopy ball on the pads, Crawley flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
EDGY! Tossed up on middle, Buttler comes down the track and looks to heave it away but it takes the inside edge and goes to deep square leg. A single.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
On a length on the pads, Buttler flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! What a shot that is! This has been a flawless innings from him so far! Back of a length ball outside off, Crawley hammers it through the covers for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on off, Crawley blocks it to point.
BEATEN! Lovely from Abbas! Good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to defend but misses.
Tossed up on middle, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.

SIX! That is terrific batting from Jos Buttler! He tried this in the previous over of Yasir but did not time but he has picked the bones out of this one. Floated on middle, Buttler dances down the track and lifts it over the bowler's head for a biggie. The umpires check whether it is a six or a four and the replays show that it is the former.
On off, pushed to cover.
SIX! This is even bigger! Buttler is in the mood now! Flighted on middle, Buttler uses his feet and thrashes it over the bowler's head for another biggie.
Tossed up on middle, Buttler blocks it back to the bowler.

FOUR! That is pure timing! Brilliant batting and end of a big over for England! Flighted ball outside off, Buttler leans forward and just drives it nonchalantly through the extra cover region for a boundary. 16 runs from the over. The ball seems to have been lost but finally Abbas and Afridi have found it. The partnership also moves to over 100. Excellent one for England!
Good length ball on off, Crawley looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it rolls to deep square leg. A couple taken.
On a length on middle, Crawley works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on the pads, Zak flicks but straight to mid-wicket.
EDGY! Good length ball on off, Crawley looks to defend but it takes the outside edge towards the slip cordon. The fielder dives and makes a good stop.
On off, pushed to point.
Good length ball on off, Crawley solidly blocks it to the cover region.

Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, Buttler rocks on his back foot and pushes it to point.

FOUR! Beautiful from Buttler! Good length ball outside off, Buttler prods forward and drives it through the covers. It is not the quickest of outfield but it gets to the fence. Moves to 48.
Floated on middle, Crawley pushes it to mid on for a single.
Loopy ball outside off, Buttler leans forward and leaves it alone.
Flatter one outside off, punched to cover.
Tossed up on off, Buttler pushes it to mid off.

FIFTY! 18TH Test fifty for Jos Buttler! He continues his good form in this series and is silencing his critics. He came in when England had lost a couple of quick wickets and has not taken England to a safe position along with Zak Crawley. Loopy ball on middle, Buttler flicks it to deep square leg for a couple.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
FOUR! Terrific! We have been a witness to some great shots from Zak Crawley today! Good length ball outside off, Crawley drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Crawley works it to wide of mid on for a single.
Good length ball on off, Buttler looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and onto the pads. A rare false shot from Buttler today.
On off, Buttler blocks it to point.
FOUR! Time for some innovation! Yasir comes around the wicket to Crawley and bowls a floated ball on middle, Crawley goes on his knees and reverse sweeps it to the deep point region for a boundary.
Goes again but there is protection in the deep this time! This is bowled on the pads, Crawley plays the reverse sweep to deep cover for a single.
Floated on the pads, Buttler flicks it to mid-wicket for a single. 250 up for England.
Short ball on middle and leg, Zak tucks it to square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Buttler pushes it to long on for a single.
Tossed up on off, Crawley drives it to long off for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Crawley defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Crawley plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Floated delivery on off, Crawley punches it towards long off for a single.
Full delivery on off, Buttler drives it through mid off for a run.
On middle, Crawley plays a reverse sweep towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
Flighted delivery on off, Zak keeps it out.
Short delivery on middle, Buttler pulls it to mid-wicket.
Floated delivery on middle, Buttler tucks it to mid-wicket.

Loopy delivery on off, Buttler keeps it out.
On middle, Buttler blocks it well.
On off, Buttler pushes it towards covers for a single.
Flatter and outside off, left alone.
On off, pushed to point.
Full delivery outside off, Buttler drives it wide of long off and collects a couple.
Gets away with it! Tossed up ball outside off, Buttler looks to slap it but has to reach for it. It goes uppishly towards long off. A single taken.
FOUR! What a sweep shot that is! Floated ball on middle, Crawley sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.

150 up for Crawley! He continues to impress with this performance. He has been flawless. This knock should make him a regular in the England side. Flatter on middle, Crawley flicks it to mid-wicket for a single. Can he score a double century?
Tossed up delivery on middle, Crawley pushes it through mid on for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Buttler pushes it through mid off for a run.
Full delivery on off, Crawley drives it through mid off for a single.
On middle, Buttler punches it through mid on for a run.

Floated delivery on off, Crawley makes room and punches it through point for a run. 150-run stand is up between Buttler and Crawley.
On middle, Buttler flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery on off, Buttler drives it through mid off for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Buttler pushes it to cover.
Flatter on off, Buttler pushes it to point and takes a single.
FOUR! Swept away and swept away nicely! He is in full control of this shot! Loopy ball on the pads, Crawley sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Tossed up on the pads, Crawley flicks it to the deep square leg region for a couple. This is excellent cricket from England.
The batsman has driven it through mid off.

Is that a drop? From the reactions of the Pakistan players, it certainly looks like it. Floated ball on off, Crawley drives it straight back to the bowler. Alam lunges forward to catch but it is a tough one and fails to hold on. The ball goes towards long off and the batters pick up a single. Tough chance.
NO BALL! Shaheen oversteps! On a length on middle, Crawley flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! Strays on the pads! Full delivery on the pads, Buttler looks to flick but it goes off his pads and past the diving keeper and into the fine leg fence.

EDGY! No Ball! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to drive but it takes the inside edge and it goes to square leg. A single. The third umpire conveys it to the on-field umpire that Shaheen has overstepped.
NO BALL! Another No ball! Poor stuff from Afridi! Full ball on middle, Crawley pushes it past the bowler and picks up a couple before the fielder cleans it up.
FOUR! This is getting clumsy from Afridi and Pakistan! Good length ball on middle, Crawley flicks it nonchalantly through mid-wicket for a boundary. 300 up for England.
BEATEN! Much better from Afridi! Good length ball outside off, angling in. Crawley looks to push but the ball sneaks in between the bat and pad, into the mitts of the keeper.
Full on middle, Crawley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on middle, worked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Very full delivery on the pads, Buttler jams it to the mid-wicket region for a single. End of a long and a poor over from Afridi.
On a good length on middle, Buttler looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Length delivery on middle, Buttler flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length and outside off, Jos offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on off, Buttler keeps it out.
Full delivery on off, Buttler drives it to mid off.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Buttler looks to defend but misses it.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Crawley looks to drive but misses it.
Full again on middle, Crawley flicks it through square leg for a run.
Full delivery on leg, Buttler looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Full delivery on off, Jos drives it to mid off.
FOUR! Throws the kitchen sink at that and fetches himself a boundary! Full delivery outside off, Buttler looks to drive but it takes the edge and goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Outside off, not played at.
On a good length on off, Crawley defends it off the back foot.

Good length delivery on off, Buttler looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It lands safely towards second slip.

Good length ball on middle and leg, Crawley looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to square leg for a single.
FOUR LEG BYES! Full delivery on the pads, Buttler looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Rizwan tries his best to stop it with a dive but fails and the ball rolls to the fine leg fence.
The batsman has driven it through mid off.
FOUR! Does not time it well but still has enough to reach the fence! Fullish ball outside off, Buttler drives it through mid off and picks up another boundary.
Full on off, Buttler solidly blocks it to mid off.
Poor batting! Could have left this alone! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to drive but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.

Good length ball outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.

Outside off, not played at. A maiden over from Naseem.
On a length and outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.

Back of a length delivery on middle, Buttler blocks it well.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Buttler looks to defend but misses it.

Outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
Abbas bowls another one outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
A couple! Good length ball on the pads, Buttler flicks it through the mid-wicket region and picks up three.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery from Abbas! Good length ball outside off, Crawley looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! What a way to raise the 200-run partnership! Brilliant! Full delivery outside off, Buttler drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on middle, Buttler blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler flicks it through mid-wicket and picks up three before Yasir Shah runs after it and cleans it up.
Good length ball outside off, not played at.
Naseem bowls a full delivery on off, Crawley pushes it to gully. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Afridi starts with a wayward delivery! Good length ball outside off, Buttler will not play at those as he leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper. Shaheen has to be closer to the batsman.
Another one which is bowled outside off, Buttler does not bother to play at that one.
Make that 4th leave in a row! Afridi bowls a good length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms
A little closer this time! On a length outside off, Buttler covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
A maiden to start! Full delivery outside the off stump line, Buttler lets it go to the keeper to see the over off.
Abbas starts with a good length ball outside off, Crawley makes a leave to this one.
Pakistan keep on dishing balls outside off. 8th ball in a row which is on that line. Full delivery outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Good length delivery on off, Zak prods forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Crawley defends this full ball on off to mid off.
Abbas dishes a good length ball on middle, Crawley solidly defends it back to the bowler.
EDGY! Good end to the over! Full delivery outside off, Crawley looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and it rolls to point. Another maiden.
First runs of the day! Short ball outside off, Buttler punches it through the cover region and collects a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Back of a length ball on off, Buttler drives it to cover.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Too wide from Afridi! He has to make the batsman play! Full delivery outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler makes another leave to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length on the middle stump line, Zak works it to mid-wicket for another dot.
Good length ball on off, Crawley leans forward and defends it out onto the pitch.
BEATEN! Beautiful ball from Crawley! Abbas is bowling really well! Good length ball around off, moving away. Crawley looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on off, Crawley blocks it out towards gully. Good probing over from Abbas comes to an end.
Afridi keeps on bowling it wide! Good length ball outside off, Buttler lets it go to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside the off stump line, Jos makes another leave to this one.
A quick single! Good length delivery on middle, Buttler tucks it to mid-wicket and takes a single. Moves into the 90s.
Full delivery outside the off stump line, Crawley has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length ball on off, Buttler moves forward and blocks it to point.
Back of a length ball on middle, Buttler tucks it to square leg.
EDGY! Full delivery on off, Buttler looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it goes to square leg. A single taken.
Abbas bowls a good length ball on middle, Crawley nudges it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery to start! Good length outside off, Crawley looks to defend but misses it altogether.
EDGY! Nicely bowled from Abbas! Good length ball around off, Crawley looks to defend but it takes the inside edge, hits the pads and rolls to the off side. Rizwan moves to catch it but fails.
Good length ball on middle, Buttler flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on the middle stump line, Buttler pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length ball around off, angling in. Buttler rocks on his back foot and plays it to mid off.

NOT OUT! It is missing the stumps! Poor review from Pakistan! Good length ball on middle and leg, angling in, Buttler looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Afridi puts up a huge appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Azhar Ali takes the review after a long time. The Ultra Edge shows no bat. What about the Ball Tracker? It shows that it is missing the stumps. Review lost.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Crawley lets it go to the keeper.
Abbas bowls a length ball on off, Crawley defends it to mid off.
Brilliant bowling and brilliant keeping as well! Good length ball around off, Crawley looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Edged but safe! Good length ball on middle, Zak looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes towards point. No harm done though.
Good length delivery on middle, Crawley blocks it back to the bowler.
Afridi starts with a good length ball on middle, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller delivery on the pads, Jos flicks it to the fine leg region for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley nudges it to mid-wicket.
Afridi dishes a full delivery on middle and leg, Crawley works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Finally, Crawley gets some runs on Day 2! He was stuck on it for a long, long time! Full delivery on the pads, Crawley flicks it to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary. Lovely shot!
Good comeback from Afridi! Good length ball around middle and leg, Crawley looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length delivery outside off, Buttler leaves it alone.

Hits the back leg! Brilliant bowling! Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to defend but it hits the back leg and goes to the keeper who pouches it. The keeper is interested but the bowler is not. The replays show that it has gone off the back leg.
On off, Buttler solidly defends it to cover.
Full delivery outside off, Jos shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on off, Buttler blocks it back to the bowler.
End of another excellent over from Abbas! Fullish on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on the pads, Crawley works it to square leg for a dot.
A single now! On a length outside off, Zak punches it to the cover-point region and collects a single.
Half-stop! Saved a certain boundary! Full delivery on off, Buttler drives it towards mid off. Azhar dives and makes a half-stop. Before the fielder can cut it off, the batters take three.

FOUR! Excellent shot! This is turning out to be a good over for England! Back of a length ball outside off, Crawley stands tall and punches it through the cover region for a boundary. The partnership now is 222 which is the highest for the 5th wicket for England against Pakistan.
Outside off, not played at.
FOUR! What a shot that is! Buttler moves to 99! Good length ball outside off, Buttler creams the drive through the covers for a boundary. 350 up for England.
Good length ball on off, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Lovely ball from Abbas! On a length around off, Buttler looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge. Rizwan too fails to collect.
Good length ball outside off, Buttler is in no hurry as he leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! Thank God for the DRS, Buttler must be thinking! Very fortunate. Excellent use of the review. Nothing is going right for Pakistan at the moment. Good length ball outside off, Buttler looks to defend but it seems to have taken the edge back to the keeper. Rizwan is confident and puts in a huge appeal. The umpire agrees and raises his finger. Buttler is disappointed and he reviews. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that the noise was of the bat hitting the bat and there was daylight between the bat and the ball. What a relief for Jos Buttler!

There it is! 2nd Test century for Jos Buttler! He would have had his heart in his mouth the previous ball but he will be relieved that he got his century. Back of a length ball outside off, Buttler creams the drive through the cover region for three to reach the milestone. He removes his helmet and acknowledges the applause from his teammates. This is Buttler's first Test 100 since 2018.
Length delivery on leg, Buttler looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.

Crawley is walking off to a huge round of applause from not only his teammates but also from the Pakistani dressing room.

England put up an appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Masood consults his partner and takes the review. The Ultra Edge shows no bat and the Ball Tracker shows all reds. Masood has to go.
