OUT! CAUGHT! Anderson gets another and he is inching closer to 600 wickets in Tests. Pakistan have started miserably. They have already lost 2 wickets and we are only in the 5th over. This is another lovely delivery from Jimmy. Good length ball around off, Abid looks to defend but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge. It goes towards third slip where Sibley takes a good low catch. That's the advantage of standing a little ahead in the slips.
Good length ball on the pads, Azam gets off the mark by flicking it to fine leg for a couple.
BEATEN! Another lovely delivery from Anderson! Good length ball around off, Azam looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball on middle, Azam works it to square leg.
FOUR! What a shot that is! Azam makes it look so easy! Full delivery on middle, Azam drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Azam blocks it to point.
On a length on the pads, Azhar looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Again! Good length delivery on middle and leg, Azhar looks to work it on the leg side but misses. It hits him on the thigh pad.
Broad dishes a good length delivery outside off, Ali lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to it.
Well bowled! Good length ball on middle and leg, tailing in. Azhar attempts to put bat on ball but misses to get hit on the pads.
Outside off, not played at.
Full delivery on off, Babar looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes towards gully. No run.
Full delivery on middle, Babar works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Azam does not bother to play at that one.
On the pads, Azam nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Inside edge! Good length ball around off, Azhar looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Full delivery outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Archer starts with a good length ball on off, Azam blocks it to cover.
Archer bowls a good length ball on middle, Babar flicks it to the leg side.
Fuller one on middle, BA pushes it to mid on.
BEATEN! That's a corker of a delivery from Archer! Length ball around off, Babar looks to defend but it beats the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper.

TWO WIDES! That's flown over Buttler's head! Archer bowls a bouncer around middle, Babar ducks under it. Buttler hops but fails to collect. The batters collect a couple of byes. It is also called a wide.
WOW! What a delivery from Archer! Brilliant stuff! Ali had no answer to it. Good length ball around off, angling in. Ali looks to block but the ball goes through to the keeper.
On middle, Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Azam works it to the leg side.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Anderson! He dishes a good length ball around off, Azam fails to defend as it beats the outside edge.
Full delivery outside off, Babar shoulders arms to it.
Nicely punched off the back foot! Back of a length ball outside off, Azam punches it through cover and collects a couple.
Full ball on middle, Babar tucks it to square leg and picks up a single.
Outside off, not played at.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Azam shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Azam offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on middle, Azam flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Archer bowls a bouncer outside off, Azhar lets it sail through to the keeper.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review as it flicked the elbow! Good length ball around off, Azhar looks to defend at first but then decides to leave it alone. There was a noise as it passed the bat. Root is convinced that there is a noise and he takes the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and shows that it is hitting the elbow. England lose a review.
Down the leg side, Ali looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length delivery on off, Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Azam offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery outside off, Babar does not bother to play at that.
On a length on off, Azam looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes safely towards the slip region.

OUT! LBW! Anderson gets his 596th Test wicket! What a delivery this is and what a bowler Anderson is. Pakistan's talisman has to go. Good length ball on off, angling in. Azam looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Anderson appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Babar does not review as he knows that he is a goner. The Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on hitting the stumps. With that, IT IS STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Shafiq is underway straightaway! Anderson starts with a good length ball on middle, Shafiq looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards the point region. He is off the mark with a single.
Broad starts with a good length ball on off, Shafiq prods forward and blocks it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Asad blocks it to point off the front foot.
Broad bowls a back of a length ball on off, Shafiq blocks it out onto the pitch.
EDGY BUT SAFE! Good length ball on off, tailing away. Shafiq looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to point. No run.

Nicely driven from Shafiq! Confident shot! Full delivery outside off from Broad, Shafiq leans forward and drives it through the cover region. The fielder chases after it and cleans it up. Three taken.
Good length ball on middle, Azhar solidly blocks it back to the bowler.
Inside edge saves Shafiq! That would have been plumb if he had missed it! Good length ball on off, Shafiq looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards deep square leg. A single taken.
Good length ball down the leg side, Azhar looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on off, Azhar blocks it off the front foot.
On a length on middle, Ali tucks it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another wicket falls! Anderson is just three wickets from getting his 600th Test wicket. This was a nothing shot from Asad Shafiq and Pakistan slip further. Poor cricket from the visitors. Anderson is having the time of his life out there. He dishes a good length ball around off, moving away. Shafiq could have left that alone but he looks to defend. It takes the outside edge and goes towards Root at first slip. He makes no mistake and Pakistan are 4 down with just 30 on the board.
Anderson dishes a full delivery on off, nipping in. Alam blocks it to cover. End of a successful over from Anderson.
Good length ball on off, Ali looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and goes to the leg side. A single taken.
Good length ball on middle, Alam pushes it back to the bowler.
LEG BYE! Alam will have to wait to get off the mark! On a length on the pads, Alam shuffles across and looks to flick. It goes off his pads towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Good length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review! It is missing leg stump! Broad was convinced and he convinces Root to take the review! Good length ball on middle and leg, Azhar looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Broad puts up a huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Broad is interested and tells Root to take the review. There is nothing on Ultra Edge and the Ball Tracker shows that it is missing the leg stump. Poor decision to review.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball on off, Alam defends it with a dead bat.
Anderson hits the deck hard on middle and off, Fawad defends it off the inner half of his bat.
On off, Alam keeps it out.

A huge sigh of relief as Fawad Alam has got his first run in Test cricket in more than a decade! Fuller ball on off, Fawad defends it with soft hands to the off side and calls for a quick single. He gets it with ease. This run will calm his nerves and now he will start looking a bit more confident.
Outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
Good length ball away from the stumps and the Pakistan skipper is happy to let that go.
Full delivery outside off, Alam watches the ball carefully and leaves the ball alone.
Did it carry? No, it did not! Good length ball on off, Alam looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards second slip. Luckily for Alam, it lands short.
Full delivery on off, Alam pushes it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Alam looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Probably going a bit too high.
Broad bowls another length ball on middle, Fawad flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Azhar nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery on off, Azhar Ali prods forward and blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Azhar flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Azhar looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
On a length outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to it.
A single! Anderson bowls a length ball on off, Azhar leans forward and pushes it to point for a single.
BEATEN! Beats the outside edge again! Good length ball outside off, Alam looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball on off, Azhar pushes it through the cover-point region and collects a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Full delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! That is a lovely delivery from Broad! Good length ball around off, Ali attempts to put bat on ball but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Ali makes a leave to this one.
Good length ball on off, Azhar defends it to cover.
BEATEN! Beauty from Anderson! Good length ball around off, Alam looks to defend but misses it completely.
Again! Anderson has his tail up! On a length outside off, Alam is looking to defend off his back foot but gets beaten again.
Full on middle, Alam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Alam lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Fawad pushes it to mid on.
Fullish ball on the pads, Alam flicks it to the deep square leg region and picks up a couple before the fielder cleans it up.
Good length ball well outside off, it comes in a bit but still away. Azhar does not disturb that.
This time Broad bowls it on the off stump line. Azhar defends it with a straight bat.
Broad now deliberately goes full on off. Azhar pushes it to mid off.
Good leave! Length ball outside off, it comes back in. Azhar lunges forward and shoulders arms to it. The ball just about misses the off pole and Broad cannot believe it.
Now on off, Azhar Ali keeps it out.
Fuller on off, the Pakistan Test skipper gets on his front foot and keeps it out.
Full delivery on off, Fawad moves forward and then defends it to point.
Good length ball on off, Alam blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Alam works it to square leg and collects a single.
Full delivery outside off, Ali has no problems in leaving it alone.
Outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
BEATEN! What a delivery from Anderson! Full delivery outside off, inviting Ali for the drive. Azhar obliges and goes for it but fails to get any bat on it.
Archer starts with a full delivery outside off, Alam shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Alam looks to defend at first and then decides to get his bat away.
Fullish on off, Fawad plays it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Alam defends it out onto the pitch.
BEATEN! Excellent from Archer! He has started well here! Good length ball outside off, Alam looks to defend but gets beaten.
Archer runs and bowls a length ball at 144.4 kph on middle, Alam looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. A maiden to start from Archer.
Some swing straightaway for Woakes! Good length ball outside off, swinging away. Azhar lets it go to the keeper.

No Ball! Good length ball on off, keeping a little low. Ali looks to defend but it takes the bottom edge and hits the pads. Woakes has overstepped and the third umpire conveys it to the on-field umpire.
Good length ball outside off, Ali makes a leave to this one.
Another length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar lets it go to the keeper.

Excellent fielding! Saved a run there! Very full delivery outside off, Ali drives it through the point region. Pope runs after it and dives forward to pull it back before it reaches the fence. Three taken.
A dot to end the over! Good length ball outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
FOUR! That's nicely clipped away from Ali! Archer starts with a good length ball on the pads, Ali is very good on the leg side and he flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.

A big appeal for LBW turned down! Probably going down the leg side. A yorker on the pads, Ali looks to defend but misses and goes onto hit the pads. Archer and England put up an appeal but the umpire shakes his head. England don't take the review. Good decision as the Ball Tracker shows that it is missing the leg stump.
A bouncer around middle, Azhar ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off, Ali lets it go to the keeper.
Full outside off, left alone.
Ali leaves this good length ball outside off alone.
Good length ball outside off, Alam lets it go to the keeper.
A quick single! Full delivery on off, Alam flicks it to square leg. There was a bit of hesitation for a single but they take the single in the end.
Good length ball on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
EDGY! Well bowled from Woakes! On a length on off, Alam attempts to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes through the gully region. Two taken.

Gets through the slips! Full delivery outside off, Alam looks to block but it takes the outside edge. The third slip fielder tries to stop it but fails. Burns chases after it and slides to make a stop. The umpires check whether it is a clean save and the replays show that it is. Three runs.
Good length ball on middle, Ali looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full delivery outside off, Alam shoulders arms to it.
Good length delivery outside off, Alam looks to defend at first but moves his bat away.
Archer bowls this one way outside the off stump, Alam has no problems in leaving it alone.
On a length outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
Much-better from Archer! Good length ball on middle and leg, Alam attempts to defend but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length ball down the leg side, Fawad looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball down the leg side, Azhar looks to play the flick shot but misses.
Excellent yorker but extremely well played! Woakes bowls this one on middle, Ali manages to dig it out to the square leg region.
Good length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
A couple here! On a length on the pads, Ali tucks it to deep square leg and picks up an easy couple.
Full delivery on off, Ali pushes it to point.
Short ball on middle, Ali pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length ball on middle, Ali flicks it wide of short leg and picks up a single.
Short ball around middle and leg, Fawad ducks under it.
Short and outside off, Alam punches it but straight to the point fielder.
Archer bends his back and bowls a bouncer around middle, at 92 mph. Alam ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Alam tucks it to square leg for a single.

NOT OUT! Hits the shoulder! This though is a corker of a delivery from Jofra Archer! He is really cranking it up at the moment. Archer bowls a bouncer around off, Ali is surprised by it and hops to defend but he seems to have missed it. England think that there was a noise and appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Root asks Buttler whether to take the review and at the last moment, he takes it. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that it hit the shoulder of Ali before it went to the keeper. England have lost all their reviews now.
Bess starts with a floated delivery on off, Alam keeps it out.
Flighted and slower outside off. Fawad defends it.
Short and quicker now outside off. Fawad gets on his back foot and cuts it but finds point.
Little bit of bounce now for Bess. It is on middle and off, Alam keeps it out.

FOUR! Good shot and this is how they need to bat. Respect the good balls but when there is a loose ball, punish it. Bess is guilty of bowling short and wide outside off. Fawad Alam gets on his back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Darts it quicker on middle and leg. A spin bowler's gentle angry response. Alam blocks it out to get through the over.
Good length ball on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Short ball outside off, Ali pushes it to cover.
BYE! Short ball around middle, Ali ducks under it. Buttler jumps to collect but fails. The ball rolls to fine leg and the batters steal a bye.
Back of a length on middle, Alam defends it out onto the pitch.
Bouncer! It is bowled around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Short ball on middle, Alam pulls it to deep mid-wicket and picks up three to keep the strike for the next over.
Floated on middle, Alam defends it to short leg.
Tossed up on middle, Alam prods forward and blocks it to the bowler.
Quicker ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off, Fawad drives it straight to cover.
Outside off, cut to point for another dot.
Full on the pads, Alam works it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full delivery outside off, Alam lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on off, Alam pushes it to mid off.
On the pads, Fawad flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length on middle, Ali works it to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Ali blocks it wide of cover and takes a single.
Good length ball on middle, Alam tucks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on middle, Azhar pushes it to mid on.
Flatter one on off, Ali plays it to deep cover for a single.
Down the leg side, Alam looks to flick but misses.
Quicker one on middle, Alam blocks it back to the bowler.
Short ball around off, Alam moves inside his crease and then cuts it to point.
Tossed up on off, Alam prods forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good piece of fielding! Woakes has not got his line right yet! Good length delivery on the pads, Ali flicks it to fine leg. Anderson runs across and makes a good diving stop. Keeps it down to two.
Full delivery on off, Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Ali blocks it to cover.
Woakes bowls another full one on middle, Azhar plays it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on middle, Azhar punches it to mid on.
Floated on off, Alam defends it to cover.
On off, Alam prods forward and defends it to the off side.
Quicker one on middle, Fawad gets his bat down in time and blocks it to mid on.
Shorter and outside off, Alam punches it to cover.
Flighted on off, Alam defends it to short leg.
Flatter and outside off, Alam cuts it to point.
Good length ball on off, Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Azhar solidly defends it to mid on.
Fuller one outside off, Ali has no problems in leaving it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Ali punches it to cover for nothing.
Good length ball outside the off stump line, Ali covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Excellent ball from Woakes! This was a much-better over from him! Good length ball outside off, angling away. Ali looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Flatter on off, Azam pushes it to cover.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Beautifully bowled from Bess! Bowls it on the rough and gets the reward. Fawad Alam's fight is over in this innings and he walks back to the pavilion. Pakistan are struggling. Bess flights this one on off, it spins away. Fawad Alam prods forward in an attempt to defend. It takes the faintest of edges back to Buttler who takes a good catch. England appeal and up goes the finger. Alam knew it as well and turns back to go to the pavilion. He fought hard in the middle but needed to stay there a bit longer.
Short ball down the leg side, Rizwan lets it go to the keeper.
Full on middle, Rizwan pushes it to mid on.
Flatter one on middle, Mohammad defends it out onto the pitch.
Full on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
On a length on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar pushes it to cover.
Good length ball on off, Ali drives it to cover and takes a single.
On off, Rizwan blocks it to point.
Loopy ball on middle, Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Azhar prods forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
On middle, Ali tucks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted on the middle stump line, Ali nudges it to the leg side.
Full on middle, Azhar pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Ali works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Ali blocks it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, pushed to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Ali flicks it to the deep square leg region for a couple.
Back of a length ball on middle, Ali defends it solidly off the back foot.
BEATEN! Excellent nut from Broad! Good length ball outside off, Ali looks to defend but the ball moves away but misses.
Good length ball on the pads, Ali tucks it to square leg.
Full delivery outside off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up ball on middle, Rizwan defends it back to the bowler.
Beautiful delivery from Bess! Floated ball around off, spinning in. Rizwan prods forward to defend but it hits the thigh pad and goes past the keeper. Two leg byes taken.
Flatter one on middle, Rizwan defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! No man in the deep and Rizwan fetches a boundary! Loopy ball on middle, Rizwan sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan pulls it to fine leg and picks up three before the fielder cuts it off.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan blocks it to cover.
Full delivery outside off, Rizwan pushes it to point.
On a length on off, Rizwan drives it to the cover region where the fielder dives to make a good stop.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full ball on middle, Rizwan blocks it to the leg side.
On off, Rizwan solidly blocks it to cover.
Flatter one on middle, Azhar tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely swept from Ali! Bess tosses this on off, Ali goes on his knees and sweeps it. There is no fielder in the deep on the leg side and Ali fetches himself a boundary.
Quicker one on middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Azhar flicks it to the leg side.
Tosses this one on middle, Ali nudges it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Poor ball! It was short and wide and got what it deserved! Bess bows it way outside off, Ali cuts it through the point region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish on off, Mohammad drives it straight to cover.
Full on off, Rizwan drives it to mid off. Archer dives and saves some runs for his side. Good fielding.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball outside off, Mohammad has no problems in leaving it alone.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball around off, angling in. Rizwan looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. England appeal but the umpire says no. England think but what are they thinking about as there are no reviews left? The Ball Tracker shows that the impact is outside off.
Full delivery on off, Ali pushes it to mid off.
Another full one on middle, Azhar drives it past the bowler and takes a single.
On the pads, Rizwan flicks it to the fine leg region and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Mohammad blocks it to cover.
On a length on middle, Rizwan blocks it solidly back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! That bounced a little extra! Good length ball outside off, it bounces more than expected. Ali looks to punch it off the back foot but fails to get any bat on it.
Full delivery on off, Azhar lunges forward and blocks it to cover.
A couple now! On a length on off, Ali guides it through the gully region and picks up a couple. 100 up for Pakistan.
Good length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on off, Azhar blocks it to point.
Good length ball on middle, Rizwan blocks it back to Anderson.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Full delivery on the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Full on middle, Mohammad defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish down the leg side, Rizwan looks to flick but misses.
Full on off, Rizwan lunges forward and defends it to mid off.

Was there an edge on that? From the looks of Anderson and Root, it looks like it. Good length ball outside off, Rizwan looks to defend but it seems to have gone off the outside edge towards the keeper. Buttler tumbles to collect but it falls short.
Warm up delivery as it is in the 80s mph. Good length ball on off, Azhar defends it off his back foot.
Just about 90 mph this one. This one is around middle and off, Azhar defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Ali leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! Milestone boundary for Azhar Ali as he crosses 6000 runs in Test cricket. Good length ball on off, Azhar looks to play on the off side but the ball goes off the outside edge and away from the slip to the third man fence. A lot of pressure on the skipper heading into this innings but he has fought his demons so far and is giving some respectability to his side's total and is continuing to fight.
Length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Fullish on off, the Pakistan Test skipper blocks it to get through the over.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan blocks it to point.
FOUR! Carved away from Rizwan! Short ball outside off, Rizwan cuts it through cover-point and it races away to the fence. Rizwan is looking good.
On a length on middle, Mohammad blocks it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Mohammad blocks it to the point region.
Full delivery on off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Mohammad defends it onto the pitch.
Good length ball on middle, Azhar plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Cut away and cut away nicely! This is poor bowling and Ali moves to 48! Good length ball outside off, Ali cuts it through the gully region for a boundary.
Short ball around middle, Ali ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on off at 87 mph. Ali stands tall and defends it to cover.
Bouncer bowled around middle. It is bowled at 87 mph. Ali does well to duck under it.

FOUR! FIFTY! 32nd one for Ali in Tests! Flicked away nicely! Good length ball on the pads, Azhar flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary. This brings up the 50 for Azhar Ali. A welcome return to form for the Pakistan skipper. He has fought hard and needs to continue. Not much of a celebration as he knows that his job is not done yet.
Full on middle and leg, Rizwan pushes it to mid on.
On the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but the ball hits his thigh pad and goes to the leg side. They take a leg bye.
Good length ball on off, Azhar defends it.
Length ball on off, Azhar punches it to cover.
Away from off, Ali cuts it but now finds point.
FOUR! Tickled away! Good length ball on off, Azhar opens the face of the bat in the last minute and guides it away from slip for a boundary.
That is nasty! Right on the helmet! Archer bowls a bouncer on middle, Rizwan looks to sway away but gets hit on the helmet. This was a pacy delivery from Archer.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan solidly blocks it onto the pitch.
Good length ball on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Short one around middle, Mohammad ducks under it.
Full delivery outside off, Rizwan pushes it to cover.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan blocks it to the off side.

FOUR! Beautifully played from Ali! Stylish shot! Back of a length ball outside off, Ali cuts it through point for another boundary. The partnership between these two move to 50. These two are fighting hard but they need to continue on and get a big partnership just like Buttler and Crawley did for England.
Good length ball on middle, Ali tucks it to square leg for a single.
On off, Rizwan pushes it to gully for a single.

OVERTHROWS! Unnecessary runs from England! Good length ball on off, Ali defends it to deep point and takes off for a single. The fielder throws a wild one back towards the keeper and it goes towards deep mid-wicket. Four runs added to the total.
Good length ball on off, Ali pushes it to silly mid off.
Full on middle, driven back to the bowler.
Short ball around middle, Rizwan ducks under it.
Back of a length on off, Rizwan hops and defends it onto the pitch.
Nicely punched away! Short ball outside off, Rizwan punches it through the cover region and picks up three before the fielder cuts it off.
FOUR! Pulled away in disdain! Short ball on middle, Ali pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Short and around middle, Ali ducks under it.
NO BALL! Back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan defends it out onto the pitch. Woakes has overstepped.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan pushes it to point for a single.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Ali looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards the square leg region.

An appeal for LBW! Turned down! England have no reviews left. This looked close! Good length ball on off, Ali looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. England appeal but nothing from the umpire. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it was umpire's call on impact.
On a length ball on middle, Ali plays it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Azhar solidly blocks it to cover.
Flighted on off, Rizwan defends it to the short leg fielder.
Tossed up on off, Mohammad prods forward and defends it out.
Quicker one on off, Rizwan blocks it to mid off.
Full one on off, defended out onto the pitch.
Flatter on off, Mohammad pushes it to the deep point region for a single.
Floated on middle, Ali flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Ali defends it to silly mid on.
Good length ball down the leg side, Ali looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on off, Azhar prods forward and defends it to the point region.
Very full delivery down the leg side, Ali looks to flick but fails to get any bat on it.
Full on middle, Azhar pushes it to mid on.
Poor line! Good length ball on the pads, Ali tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Nicely played! Flatter one outside off, Ali guides it to the point region and picks up three before the fielder cuts it off.
Flatter one on middle, Rizwan blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter and outside off, Rizwan punches it to deep cover for a single.
Quicker one on off, Ali blocks it out onto the pitch.
FOUR! Swept away nicely! Ali has used the sweep shot well against Bess! Tossed up on middle, Ali bends on his knees and sweeps it to the deep square leg region for a boundary. 150 up.
On off, defended off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan guides it wide of point and takes a single.
Good length ball on middle, Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Azhar pushes it to the point region.
On a length on middle, Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
Outside off, not played at.
FOUR! Steered it deliberately! Well played! Full delivery outside off, Ali steers it through gully for a boundary.
Full and outside off, Rizwan pushes it to cover.
Floated on off, Mohammad defends it to point and takes a single.
Tossed up on off, Ali blocks it to the bowler.
On middle, Azhar prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, Ali solidly defends it to short leg.

Was there an edge? No, there is not as the replays show that it has hit the back thigh pad. Bess bowls a floated ball around off, Ali looks to defend but it goes off the thigh pad. Buttler fails to collect it cleanly. Bess has his hands on his head but it had gone off the thigh pad. With that, it is TEA ON DAY 3.
Broad starts with a full delivery on middle, Rizwan pushes it back to the bowler.
First run of the session! Good length ball on off, Mohammad drives it wide of mid off and picks up a single.
EDGY! Good length ball on middle, Ali looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it goes to deep square leg. A single taken.
Full delivery on the pads, Rizwan flicks it to square leg.
On a length on middle, Mohammad blocks it back to the bowler for a dot.
Full delivery on the pads, Rizwan flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan blocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Thrashed! Positive start from Rizwan! Back of a length ball outside off, Rizwan hammers it through the cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Mohammad blocks it to cover.

FOUR! What a shot that is from Rizwan! Perfect shot from the Pakistan wicket-keeper! Full delivery on middle, Rizwan drives it straight past the bowler and into the fence for another boundary in the over. Rizwan continues to impress.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan blocks it to the cover region.
Length ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler.

That is very close! But England are out of their reviews! Full delivery on middle and leg, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. England put up an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it is missing the leg stump. Another excellent decision by Michael Gough, one of the on-field umpires.
On middle, Azhar flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Ali pushes it to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Ali tucks it to the fine leg region for a single.
Full delivery on off, Mohammad blocks it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Rizwan solidly blocks it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! What a beauty from Archer! Good length ball outside off, moving away. Ali looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Back of a length ball on off, Azhar defends it to the off side.
Short ball on the off stump line, Ali defends it to cover.
On the pads, Azhar looks to flick but it goes off his pads towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Good length ball on middle, Rizwan tucks it to deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Beautifully played! Archer is quick but is still able to play that well! Short ball outside off, Ali guides it over the slip cordon and into the third man fence. 100-run partnership is up between the two. A brilliant one for Pakistan but they have a long way to go and cannot throw their wickets away.
Full on middle, Rizwan plays it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Rizwan blocks it to mid on for another dot.
On a length on the pads, Mohammad nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
On middle, driven to mid off.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan looks to pull but does not time it well. It lands in the mid-wicket region and the batsmen collect a single.
Short of a length on off, Rizwan pushes it to point off the back foot.
On a length on middle, Rizwan defends it solidly back to the bowler.
FOUR! Excellent batting from Rizwan! This is poor bowling from Archer! Short ball around off, Rizwan waits for it and then upper cuts it over the keeper's head for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan lets it go to the keeper.
On off, pushed to point.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes through gully. A couple of runs added to the total of Pakistan.
Floated on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on the pads, worked to short leg.
Full and outside off, Ali sweeps it to deep square leg and picks up an easy couple. Moves into the 90s.
Flatter on middle, Ali tucks it to short leg.
Floated on off, defended off the front foot.
Outside off, pushed to point.
Short one around middle, Rizwan ducks under it.
Another short one which is bowled around middle, Rizwan manages to duck under it. 2nd bouncer of the over.
Outside off, not played at.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, ducked under.
Good length ball outside off, Mohammad leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, guided to third man for a single.
Tossed up on off, Rizwan defends it off the front foot.
Shortish around off, Rizwan punches it through cover-point and gets three as the outfield is slow and the fielder mops it up.
Flighted on off, Ali keeps it out.
Too straight as this one is on middle. Ali defends it with ease.
Better from Bess. Gives this one air and bowls it just outside off. Ali taps it to backward point.
Azhar moves to 93! Flighted and full around off. Ali drives it through covers. The ball does not have the legs to reach the fence and he gets three.
Back of a length on middle, Ali works it to mid on and takes a single.
Short ball around middle, Rizwan ducks under it.
Short and around off, Mohammad taps it to gully.
Comes around the wicket and bowls a length ball on middle, Rizwan defends it out onto the pitch.
Another bouncer which is bowled around middle and leg, Rizwan is not bothered as he ducks under it.
Short on middle, Rizwan defends it to gully.
Flatter on the pads, Azhar flicks it to fine leg for a single.

SIX! What a way to reach his 3rd Test fifty! He is having a wonderful series. He scored one in the last Test and continues his form in this match as well. He will look to make it a huge one now. Floated outside off, Rizwan dances down the track and hammers it over long off for a biggie. 200 up for Pakistan.
PLAY AND A MISS! Short and outside off, Rizwan looks to cut but misses.
Flighted on off, defended to point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Tossed up on off, Rizwan blocks it out.
Good length ball on middle, Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Ali drives it past the bowler and it goes onto hit the stumps at the bowler's end.
Short ball on off, Azhar defends it onto the pitch.
FOUR! Moves to 99 with a lovely shot! Woakes is not having a good time with the ball! Good length ball on the pads, Ali works it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Azhar tucks it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Ohh ho! Almost! Brilliant delivery from Woakes! Good length ball around off, Ali looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Takes the single! Loopy ball on off, Rizwan guides it to the third man region for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Azhar blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on off, Ali is in no hurry as he defends it out onto the pitch.

FOUR! Hundred for Azhar Ali! What a knock this has been! A captain's knock from the Test skipper and he has silenced his critics and doubters with the bat. A lot of pressure heading into the Test, chips were down when he came out to bat but like a true leader he has shown his troops how to fight and battle it out in the middle and given his side a glimmer of hope. A much-needed century for him. He gets to his 17th Test ton in style. Floated delivery on off, Azhar gets on his front foot and drives it through covers for a boundary. He raises his bat, removes his helmet and has a huge smile on his face. His teammates are up on their feet and he looks at the sky.  The job is not done though and he will need to carry on his effort.
On the stumps, Azhar regains his focus and defends it.
On the pads, Azhar glances it to the on side and keeps the strike with a single.
Full ball outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Full on off, Azhar defends it on the front foot.
Full on off, Ali defends it right under his eyes.
Slowish delivery on the stumps, Azhar keeps it out.
Full again on off, Ali defends it.
Good solid block to end the over. It is once again full on the stumps, Azhar lunges forward and taps it onto the ground.
Tossed up on off, Rizwan blocks it to cover.
Floated on the pads, Rizwan sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Full on the pads, Ali works it to the leg side for a single.
Quicker one on off, Rizwan defends it back to the bowler.
Full on off, pushed to long on for a single.
Flatter on the pads, Ali looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! What a catch from Jos Buttler! Excellent stuff from the England keeper! This was a nothing delivery and it has fetched Woakes a wicket. Rizwan will feel unlucky and he has to go after playing a gutsy knock but he needed to be out there. Woakes dishes a good length ball on the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but it goes off the edge towards the left of the keeper. Buttler dives to that side and takes a magnificent catch. England appeal and up goes the finger. Rizwan has to walk back.
Poor shot from Yasir! Good length ball outside off, Yasir looks to poke at it but fails to get any bat on it.
Yasir is off the mark! Good length ball outside off, Yasir guides it through the gully region for a couple.
BEATEN! BEAUTY! Good length ball around off, Yasir looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Full delivery on middle, Yasir pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Yasir lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, Ali lets it go to the keeper.
Flatter on middle, Azhar plays it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Azhar tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery outside off, Yasir pushes it through the point region for a couple.
Short ball on middle, Ali pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full delivery on off, Shah defends it onto the pitch.
Back of a length ball on middle, Yasir flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Straight to the fielder! Good length ball outside off, Ali cuts but straight to the point fielder.
Full delivery outside off, Ali leaves it alone. The ball wobbles after pitching and Buttler fails to collect it. He seems to have hurt himself but is fine to continue.
Floated on the pads, Shah sweeps it to the fine leg region. The fielder collects and throws it to the keeper but the batter was well in.
FOUR! Floated ball on off, Shah looks to defend but it goes past the keeper and into the third man fence.
Tossed up on middle, Yasir flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter on middle, Yasir flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Full on the pads, Azhar nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Full on middle, blocked out.
Back of a length ball on middle, Azhar flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length on middle, Shah tucks it to square leg.
Full on middle, Shah blocks it back to the bowler.
Good shot from Shah! Full delivery on middle, Yasir drives it past the bowler. Archer chases after it from mid on but cannot stop the batters from taking three.
Good length ball on off, Azhar blocks it to cover.
FOUR! CREAMS THE DRIVE! Very full delivery outside off, Ali leans forward and drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Anderson starts with a length ball on middle, Shah defends it back to the bowler.
Anderson bowls an out-swinger outside off, Shah leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Beautiful nut from Anderson! Good length ball around off, moving away. Shah looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
This is poor batting! Good length ball outside off, angles away. Shah looks to poke at it but misses it altogether.
FOUR! Pulled away nicely from Shah! Short ball on middle, Yasir pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Shah looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it goes to square leg. A single taken.
Back of a length ball on off, Shah defends it to cover off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! The new ball does the trick for England! This is a good catch from Joe Root as it was travelling quickly. Broad gets his first wicket. Beautiful delivery from Broad and he fully deserves the wicket. Good length ball around off, moving away. Shah looks to defend but it bounces extra and it takes the outside edge. It goes to first slip where Root takes it over his head. England just three wickets away from bowling Pakistan out.
Afridi is off the mark! Good length ball on the pads, Afridi flicks it to the deep square leg region for a couple.
Short ball on off, Afridi taps it to the slip cordon.
Full delivery on off, Shaheen pushes it to point for a dot.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery to end a successful over! Good length ball outside off, Afridi looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball on middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
On a length on the pads, Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on the pads, Ali flicks it to deep square leg and is happy to take just a single. Afridi will have to survive two balls in the over.
Full delivery outside off, Afridi leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Leave that alone, Afridi! Full delivery outside off, Afridi looks to drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Full delivery on off, Azhar prods forward and blocks it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Ali plays it over the point fielder and runs a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Inside edge saves him! Good length ball on middle and leg, Ali looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
EDGY! Good length ball on middle, Afridi looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and goes towards fine leg. A single.
Full delivery on off, Ali pushes it to mid off.
On middle, defended out onto the pitch.

BIG SHOUT! England have burned all their reviews! Good length ball on middle, Ali looks to flick but he seems to have missed. There was a noise as it passed the bat. It hits him on the pads. Anderson appeals but the umpire shakes his head. The Ultra Edge shows that there was bat on it.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Full ball on off, Ali pushes it to cover.

OUT! Caught! Brilliant! Outstanding catch from Buttler! Wow! What a turnaround, in form Buttler has had, both with the bat and with the gloves behind the stumps. Broad bangs it in short around the body. Shaheen looks to glance it fine down the leg side. The ball kisses the edge and flies to the right of Buttler. He wears his Superman boots, flies to  that side and takes a superb one-handed stunner. England 2 wickets away now from wrapping up this innings.
Length ball on off, Abbas blocks it.
Short ball around the body, Abbas ducks under it.
On the pads, Abbas looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length ball around off, Abbas defends it late from behind his body.
Down the leg side again. Buttler takes it nicely again but unlike Shaheen, Abbas does not get anything on the cherry.
Full on off, Azhar taps it back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, Ali looks to flick but misses.

EDGED AND DROPPED! FOUR! Burns at second slip is the guilty party. Not his usual position as Stokes is the one who occupies that area generally. Good length ball on off, Azhar looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge which goes to the left of Burns at second slip. It is at a good height as well but he fails to hang on. The ball goes behind and they take a run. Anderson denied his 598th Test scalp and a 5-wicket haul. The ball goes behind and to the fence.
On off, Ali plays to point and gets a single.

EDGED AND DROPPED AGAIN! Anderson cannot believe his luck and he must be fuming inside. Crawley is the culprit this time. Maybe Anderson does not have a 5-fer in his luck in this innings. Good length ball around off, Abbas has a poke at it but gets a thick outside edge which goes low to fourth slip. Crawley there gets both his hands to it but fails to grab onto it. The youngster has had such a good game so far but he fails to help his senior teammate add another 5-fer to his name.
On the stumps, Abbas manages to block it. End of a very eventful over.
Good length ball on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Majestic shot from Azhar Ali! He continues on his merry way! Short ball on middle, Ali pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
FOUR! This is even better from Ali! Broad has lost his line a bit here! Good length ball outside off, Azhar drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
Full on middle, Azhar flicks it to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Ali has just made his way in! He does not want to end his innings like that. Brilliant effort from Broad though! He bowls a good length ball on off, Ali looks to defend but it takes the inside edge onto the pads. He wants the single and takes off. Afridi obliges but seeing Broad charging in, Ali goes back. Broad collects the ball and throws it to the stumps at the keeper's end. The third umpire is called for and the replays show that Ali had made his way in.
Full on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full on middle, Abbas pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Abbas flicks it to mid--wicket.
A single now! On a length on middle, Abbas looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it goes to the deep square leg region. A single taken.
On a length on middle, defended out onto the pitch.
Good length ball on middle, Ali blocks it out. He would want to take a single now.

OUT! RUN OUT! That was absolute chaos! First a dropped catch but Abbas who was ball watching has not made his ground at the keeper's end. The frustration will not end though for Anderson! He has had three dropped catches off his bowling in his last two overs. England just one wicket away from bowling Pakistan out! Good length ball on middle, Ali pushes it uppishly towards mid on where Broad makes a mess of an easy catch. Ali who wants the single takes off but Abbas who is watching the ball is late to take off. Broad collects the ball and has a shy at the keeper's end and hits. No need for the third umpire as Abbas was well out of the crease. Broad apologizes to Anderson after that.
Down the leg side, Azhar looks to flick but misses. Again good take by Jos Buttler behind the stumps.
Outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Good shot from Azhar Ali! Fullish delivery around off, Azhar gets on his front foot and plays a lovely on-drive through mid on for a boundary.
On the pads, Azhar flicks it to the on side for one.
Hopeful appeal more than anything. Good length ball outside off, Naseem looks to defend but misses. There is a hopeful appeal but the umpire turns it down.
On the stumps, Shah negotiates it.
Good length ball on off, Azhar defends it.
Fuller on off, Azhar looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, Ali blocks it.
On the stumps, Ali defends it.
Length ball on off, Azhar keeps it out.
On the pads, Ali flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Short ball around off, Azhar pulls it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, Ali gets behind it and defends it.
Back of a length on off, Azhar flat-bats it over extra cover and gets a couple as ideally they would like to deal in even numbers.
Fuller on off, Ali pushes it to mid on.
Full outside off, Azhar swings but misses.
FOUR! Lovely shot but runs are not an issue and they will be happy to start the next over with Naseem Shah on strike! Short ball around off, Azhar whacks his pull to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball on leg and going away with the angle. Naseem looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Outside off, Naseem sways away.
Good length ball outside off, Shah leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Naseem looks to defend but misses.
BEATEN! On a length on off, Naseem looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, a catch is taken and Anderson gets his five-fer. 29th 5-fer in Tests! Brilliant stuff from Anderson! Good length ball outside off, Naseem looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes to the third slip region where Sibley takes a good low catch. PAKISTAN HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 273.

Anderson starts with a gentle loosener and Pakistan are underway! Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick but it goes off his pads towards the keeper. Buttler dives and makes a half stop. A leg bye taken.
Good length ball outside off, Abid covers his stumps and leaves the ball alone.
Full delivery outside off, Ali lets it go to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Ali makes another leave to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Abid shoulders arms to it. A watchful start from Pakistan.
A dot to end the first over! Good length ball outside off, Abid Ali carefully lets it go to the keeper. Good start from Anderson.
Back of a length delivery on leg, Masood looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.

Masood is off the mark in an edgy manner! Good length ball on off, Masood looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes through gully. Pope chases after it and cleans it up but cannot stop the batters from taking two.
On a length on middle, Masood flicks it to square leg.
Full delivery outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Shan makes a leave to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Edgy! Good length ball on off, Abid looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully.
A quick single! Good length ball on off, Ali defends it to the cover region and picks up a single.
Well played! Back of a length ball on off, Masood defends it to the off side and takes a single. Anderson runs ahead and then tries to throw it at the keeper's end but misses. Ali was well in though.
BEATEN! A beauty from Anderson! Good length ball around off, moving away. Ali looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Wayward from Anderson! Good length ball down the leg side, Ali looks to flick but fails to get any bat on it.

FIVE LEG BYES! That was really unnecessary! Good length ball on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to square leg and they take off for a leg bye. James Bracey, the substitute fielder, collects and has a shy at the bowler's end. He misses and the ball goes to the long off fence for five leg byes.
Full delivery on off, Ali drives it through point. The batsmen get two runs.

Back of a length on off, Abid looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards second slip where it falls short of Burns. We have seen it many times that the edge has not found the fielder at slips in this Test.
BEATEN! Beautiful from Broad! Good length ball outside off, Ali looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
Good length ball, angling in. Ali covers his stumps and leaves it alone.

FOUR! This is a gift from Broad! Pakistan have started positively here! They are looking for runs and not just defending! Good length ball on the pads, Ali flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets it go to the keeper.
On a length outside off, nipping in. Masood leaves it alone.

Is that a drop? It certainly looks like from the reactions from the England players! The replays show that it is  as there was a big outside edge on that and another catch is dropped off Anderson's bowling. Buttler took a blinder of a catch on Day 3 but drops a sitter today. Anderson bowls a full delivery outside off, Masood looks to drive without moving his feet but it takes the outside edge and goes towards Buttler. It wobbles and Buttler fails to hold on. Andersons's wait continues. He has his hands on his head.
Full delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets it go to the keeper.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Abid defends it back to the bowler.
Full and around off, Ali solidly blocks it to the off side.
Good length ball on middle, Abid flicks it to short leg where Bracey, the substitute, makes a good stop. Saved a few runs there.
On a length on middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Ali tucks it through the mid-wicket region and picks up three before the fielder cleans it up.
Full delivery on middle, Shan nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Ali does not bother to play at that one.
BEATEN! Another one beats the outside edge! Anderson has bowled really well but is yet to pick up a wicket in this innings! Good length ball outside off, Ali looks to defend but misses.
PLAY AND A MISS! This is poor! He could have left this alone but he goes for it. Full delivery outside off, Ali looks to drive but misses it altogether.
Good length ball on off, defended to point.
On a length on off, Abid blocks it solidly to cover.
Anderson bowls a good length ball on middle, Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Full on middle, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Shan pushes it to cover off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle, Masood plays it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery outside off, left alone by Masood.
FOUR! Squirted away! Good length ball on off, Masood plays it with soft hands and guides it through the gully region for a boundary.
BEATEN! Just past the outside edge! Back of a length ball outside off, Masood pokes at it but fails to make any connection.
Good length ball on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Nicely driven from Ali! Full delivery outside off, Abid leans forward and drives it through the mid off region. The batters pick up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Three this time! Good length ball on middle, Ali plays it through mid off and before Archer can give chase, they take three.
Good length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
PLAY AND A MISS! Nothing shot from Ali! Good length ball outside off, Ali looks to cut it but fails to make any connection.
Good length ball outside off, Abid cuts but straight to the point fielder.
On a length outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Ali punches it through the cover region and picks up a couple.

Good length ball on middle and leg, Ali looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. The Ultra Edge shows that it is going over the stumps.
Good length ball outside off, Ali looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Good length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
On a length on middle, Masood lets it go to the keeper.
Driven through mid on by the batsman.
Good length ball on middle, Masood blocks it out onto the pitch.
On middle, defended solidly.
Good length ball outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
Outside off, Abid leaves it.
On the pads, Abid tucks it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Length ball outside off, Shan looks to defend but misses.
Length ball on off, Masood defends it.
Length delivery on middle and leg, Shan turns it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Good length ball around off, it zips away from Abid. He looks to defend but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Masood shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on middle, Masood defends it back to the bowler.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball around off, angling in. Masood looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
On off, pushed to point.
Full on middle, Shan works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Abid shoulders arms to it.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Woakes! Good length ball around off, Ali looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
On off, Abid defends it.
Good length delivery on off, Abid blocks it.
Down the leg side, Abid looks to flick but the ball kisses his thigh pad and goes to Buttler to his left.
Length ball on the stumps, Abid defends it.
Full delivery on middle, Masood blocks it back to the bowler.
Archer bowls a good length ball outside off, Shan has no problems in leaving it alone.

OUT! There it is! A mountain no pace bowler has been able to scale before, Jimmy Anderson has scaled that as well. Joins an elite list of Muttiah Muralitharan, Shane Warne and Anil Kumble to become only the 4th player and the first pace bowler to get 600 Test wickets. What a milestone! Take a bow legend! With that mystical number, Anderson carves his name into history books and enters the Mount Rushmore of greatest ever Test bowlers. It has been a frustrating wait from wicket 598 to 600 but he has got it. Azhar Ali becomes a milestone victim for Jimmy and his expressions have changed. He is up in joy and has the ball in hand and waves it to the empty stands but all his teammates applaud. Finally Anderson gets a bit of help from the slip. Anderson bowls it in the channel of uncertainty around off, the ball bounces a bit off the surface which takes Azhar by surprise. He looks to defend it with a horizontal bat but the extra bounce surprises Azhar, takes the outside edge of his bat and goes to Root at widish first slip. The England skipper makes no mistakes and takes the catch. A perfect role model for all the youngsters in the world watching this game. Anderson has aged like a fine wine!
